addNativeCollateralToExistingCup(uint256.details: This function is called when native currency is sent to add to an existing cupImplements the CEI pattern (Checks-Effects-Interactions)Uses moreThanZero modifier to ensure non-zero depositsEmits DepositNativeCurrency event on successful depositIf this is the first native currency deposit for this NFT, adds address(0) to tokenIdToAssetsRequires msg.value to be greater than zero (enforced by moreThanZero modifier)Requires the NFT to exist (enforced by tokenId validation)

params.tokenId: The ID of the existing NFT to add native currency collateral to

addTokenCollateralToExistingCup(address,.details: This function will transfer the specified amount of tokens from the caller to this contractImplements the CEI pattern (Checks-Effects-Interactions)Uses nonReentrant modifier to prevent reentrancy attacksEmits DepositERC20Token event on successful depositThe caller must have approved this contract to spend their tokens before calling this function

params.amount: The amount of tokens to deposit (must be greater than 0)
params.tokenAddress: The ERC20 token contract address to deposit (must be a supported token with price feed)
params.tokenId: The ID of the existing NFT to add collateral to

burn(uint256).details: Implements the CEI pattern (Checks-Effects-Interactions)Uses nonReentrant modifier to prevent reentrancy attacksWithdraws both native currency and ERC20 tokens if they were deposited as collateralEmits WithdrawNativeCurrency and WithdrawERC20Token events for each successful withdrawalReverts if the token does not exist or if any transfer fails

params.tokenId: The ID of the NFT to burn and withdraw collateral from

params._baseSvgImageUri: Base URI for SVG images associated with NFTs
params._defaultPriceFeed: The default price feed address for native currency (ETH)
params._priceFeedAddresses: Array of Chainlink price feed addresses corresponding to each token
params._tokenAddresses: Array of ERC20 token addresses that can be used as collateral

depositMultipleAssetsAndMint(address[],u.details: Can also accept native currency via msg.value. If msg.value > 0, native currency will be included as collateralImplements the CEI pattern (Checks-Effects-Interactions)Uses nonReentrant modifier to prevent reentrancy attacksEmits DepositNativeCurrency and DepositERC20Token events for each successful depositAll token amounts must be greater than 0. Token addresses and amounts arrays must be same lengthThe caller must have approved this contract to spend their tokens before calling this functionExample usage:   depositMultipleAssetsAndMint(     [USDC_ADDRESS, DAI_ADDRESS],     [1000e6, 1000e18],     {value: 1e18} // 1 ETH   )

params.amounts: Array of amounts to deposit for each corresponding token address
params.tokenAddresses: Array of ERC20 token contract addresses to deposit as collateral

depositSingleAssetAndMint(address,uint25.details: This function will transfer the specified amount of tokens from the caller to this contractImplements the CEI pattern (Checks-Effects-Interactions)Uses nonReentrant modifier to prevent reentrancy attacksEmits DepositERC20Token event on successful depositThe caller must have approved this contract to spend their tokens before calling this function

params.amount: The amount of tokens to deposit (must be greater than 0)
params.tokenAddress: The ERC20 token contract address to deposit (must be a supported token with price feed)

getAssetValueInUsd(address,uint256).details: Uses Chainlink price feeds to get real-time token pricesApplies decimals conversion to maintain accuracy in calculationsMultiplies by 10^10 to maintain precision in calculationsHandles token decimals dynamically using IERC20Metadata interfaceReturns value in USD with 18 decimals of precision

params.tokenAddress: The address of the USDC token

returns._0: The USD value of the given USDC token amount with additional precision

params.tokenId: The ID of the token to get the assets for

returns._0: The list of assets deposited for the given token ID

params.tokenAddress: The address of the token to get the collateral for
params.tokenId: The ID of the token to get the collateral for

returns._0: The amount of collateral deposited for the given token ID and token address

params.tokenId: The ID of the token to get the listing status for

returns._0: The listing status of the given token ID

params.tokenId: The ID of the token to get the chain ID for

returns._0: The chain ID where the token is listed for sale

getTokenPriceInUsd(uint256).details: Converts TCL from 18 decimals to 8 decimals precision

params.tokenId: The ID of the token to get the price for

returns._0: The price of the token in USD with 8 decimals of precision

listForSale(uint256,uint256).details: Only callable by contract owner (manager)Emits TokenListedForSale event on successful listingReverts if the token is already listed for sale

params.chainId: The chain ID where the token is listed for sale
params.tokenId: The ID of the token to list for sale

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

removeFromSale(uint256).details: Only callable by contract owner (manager)Emits TokenRemovedFromSale event on successful removalReverts if the token is not listed for sale

params.tokenId: The ID of the token to remove from sale

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions. Can only be called by the current owner. NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby disabling any functionality that is only available to the owner.

tokenURI(uint256).details: Optimized version with reduced bytecode size and gas usage

returns._0: A base64 encoded JSON string containing the token's metadata

params.to: The address to transfer the token to
params.tokenId: The ID of the token to transfer

transferAndBurn(uint256,address).details: Implements the CEI pattern (Checks-Effects-Interactions)Uses nonReentrant modifier to prevent reentrancy attacksOnly callable by contract owner (manager)Token must be listed for sale

params.to: The address to transfer the token to
params.tokenId: The ID of the token to transfer and burn
